data.chText: 男孩儿；少年；男青年；小伙子
从我幼时至今，一切都发生了变化。
data.enText: Things have changed since I was a lad.
a group of friends that a man works with or spends free time with
to go to the pub with the lads
a lively young man, especially one who is very interested in women and having sex, drinks a lot of alcohol and enjoys sport

data.chText: 托尼这小子真是个花花公子——总是很会欣赏女人。
data.enText: Tony was a bit of a lad ─always had an eye for the women.
a person who works in a stable

tr: a male child (a familiar term of address to a boy)

example: there's a fellow at the door

value.def: A lad is a young man or boy.

example.ex: When I was a lad his age I would laugh at the strangest things...
example.tran: 我是他那样的小毛孩时，莫明其妙地就会发笑。

example.ex: Come along, lad. Time for you to get home.
example.tran: 来吧，小伙子。你该回家了。

value.tran: 小伙子；年轻人；少年；男孩

value.def: Some men refer to their male friends or colleagues as the lads .

example.ex: The lads don't  join the union because they're frightened of being victimized.
example.tran: 那几个伙计没加入工会是因为害怕成为牺牲品。
